  "support": "A large square block of a compact grey stone. Intact on all sides, but cut away in concave shape at the top and the top of the first line is lost. The upper surface is pecked nd has a single small rectangular hole in the centre. The Sides are well but roughly finished. The front is lightly pecked with a chisel. The upper right corner is lost from the front face, as is a small part of the lower left face. The fifth line has been chiselled away, probably in antiquity. Some traces of plaster/mortar can be seen on the front, and also traces of red pigment in some of the letters (noted already by Mauceri 1877).",
  "objectType": {
    "_": "block",
